  "plainText": "Moon Rock\nFood Info\n1\n10\n0\nElemental\n(non-survivor food)\nObject Info\n40\nSource\nDropped by\n()\n()\n×5-7 ×2-4 ×8-14\nCrafting\nDescription\nTransmute Marble into Moon Rock.\n×2 ( only)\nFilters\n(for ).\nMiscellaneous\n\"moonrocknugget\"\nExclusive to:\n“That rock came from the moon.”\n–Wilson\n“Just another rock to me.”\n–Willow\n“But is not cheese?”\n–Wolfgang\n“It's traveled so far...”\n–Wendy\n“A ROCK. FROM THE MOON”\n–WX-78\n“Implications of a lunar body? Interesting.”\n–Wickerbottom\n“It's uh, a moon rock.”\n–Woodie\n“\"Moon\" rock.”\n–Maxwell\n“A gift fröm Mani.”\n–Wigfrid\n“Neat!”\n–Webber\n“A little piece of sky to hold in my hand.”\n–Warly\n“Piece of Night Ball”\n–Wormwood\n“Woah! What an odd texture.”\n–Winona\n“It was hewn from solid moon.”\n–Wortox\n“Weird rock.”\n–Wurt\n“It came from outer space!”\n–Walter\n“I never would have predicted I'd see a piece of the moon up close.”\n–Wanda\nMoon Rocks are Items exclusive to Don't Starve Together. They are obtained by mining crash-landed Meteors, which have the appearance of sharp rocks striped with jagged blue cracks, or Suspicious Moonrock sculptures. Mining a Meteor Boulder will yield a Rock, a Flint, and 2 Moon Rocks. There is a 60% chance for a third, and a 30% chance for a fourth Moon Rock.\nMoon Rocks can be crafted into Moon Rock Walls, Cratered Moonrocks, Moon Dials, Moon Rock Idols and Moon Crater Turf. They are also required to repair the Moon Stone, and to complete construction on upgrading the Florid Postern to the Celestial Portal.\nMoon Rock can also be crafted by Wilson with 2 Marble after unlocking the \"Transmute Ore III\" skill.\nUsage[edit | edit source]\n×4\n×4\n×3\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×4\n×2\n×4\n×20\nConstructed by placing on\n×20\n×20\n×4\n×4\n×5\n×5\n×5\n×3\n×5\n×8\n×3\n×3\n×3\n×3\n×4\n×4\n×3\n×5\n×5\nTrivia[edit | edit source]\nOld Moon Rock icon.\nMoon Rocks are considered to be part of A New Reign, even though they were introduced before the official start of the beta branch in the ...In with the New update.\nIn the A Little Fixer Upper update, the textures for Moon Rocks and all related items were updated.\nEven though Moon Rocks are not available in the singleplayer game, Characters introduced with the Hamlet DLC have unused examination quotes for them.\n“Evidentaly, useful minerals can be extracted from it.”\n–Wagstaff\n“'TIS ROCK O' MOON BITS\"”\n–Wilba\n“Fascinating! These are nothing like the meteorites I've seen.”\n–Wagstaff\n“A ROCK O' YON MOON”\n–Wilba\nGallery[edit | edit source]\nSeveral Moon Rocks next to a Meteor Boulder.\nOld Moon Rock texture items beside some Moon Rock Walls.\nAn early texture for the Moon Rock as shown in the \"...In With The New\" update trailer.\nResourcesCraftable ItemsFood\nView or edit this template\nResources\nAttention: The following categories are only for the players look up the page based on their first impression, they have nothing to do with the actual categories/behavior/function/tags of these items\nPlants\nNatural non-living materials\nMobs Parts\nSkins\nFeathers\nBones and horns\nGems\nShadow Resources\nLunar Resources\nCraftable Resources\nNon-natural materials\nTrinkets\nLost Relics\nTransmission Items\nView or edit this template\nDon't Starve Together Craftable Items\nRegular Filters\nSurvivor Items\nWilson\nWillow\nWolfgang\nWendy\nWX-78\nWickerbottom\nWoodie\nWes\nMaxwell\nWigfrid\nWebber\nWarly\nWortox\nWormwood\nWinona\nWurt\nWalter\nWanda\nTools\nLight Sources\nPrototypers & Stations\nRefined Materials\nWeapons\nArmor\nClothing\nHealing\nMagic\nDecorations\nStructures\nStorage Solutions\nCooking\nFood & Gardening\nFishing\nSeafaring\nBeefalo Riding\nWinter Items\nSummer Items\nRain Gear\nCrafting Station Filters\nSpecial Event\nAncient Pseudoscience\nCarpentry\nCartography\nCritters\nCelestial\nBrightsmithy\nShadowcraft\nFabrication\nBottle Exchange\nCombrining Filter\nTea Brewing Filter\nSculptures\nSeasonings\nTrading\nTrading Hutch\nOfferings\nCawnival Creation\nTrin