  "wikitext": "{{Object Infobox\n|image = Moon Rock Dropped.png\n|icon = Moon Rock.png\n|craft_desctiption = ''Transmute Marble into Moon Rock.''\n|foodType =[[Elemental]] [[File:Elemental.png|32px|link=Elemental]]<br>(non-survivor food)\n|hpRestored = 10\n|hungerRestored = 1\n|sanityRestored = 0\n|droppedBy = {{pic|32|Moonrock Boulder}} {{pic|32|Smooth Meteor Boulder}}{{pic|32|Shattered Spider Hole}} [[File:Moonrock Werepig.png|24px|link=Suspicious Moonrock]] [[File:Moonrock Hound.png|24px|link=Suspicious Moonrock]] {{pic|x32|Ancient Moon Statue}} ({{Pic|24|Pickaxe}})</br> {{pic|32|Sunken Chest}} ({{Pic|24|Hammer}}) </br> [[File:Celestial Champion Phase 1.png|24px|link=Celestial Champion]]&times;5-7 [[File:Celestial Champion Phase 2.png|24px|link=Celestial Champion]]&times;2-4 [[File:Celestial Champion Phase 3.png|24px|link=Celestial Champion]]&times;8-14\n|stack = 40\n|spawnCode = \"moonrocknugget\"\n|filter = {{Pic32|Wilson Filter}}\n|ingredient1 = Marble\n|multiplier1 = 2 ({{Pic|28|Wilson Portrait|Wilson}} only)\n|skill = Transmute Ore III\n|skillOwner = Wilson\n}}{{Exclusivity|Don't Starve Together}}\n{{Quotes\n|wilson = That rock came from the moon.\n|willow = Just another rock to me.\n|wolfgang = But is not cheese?\n|wendy = It's traveled so far...\n|wx78 = A ROCK. FROM THE MOON\n|wickerbottom = Implications of a lunar body? Interesting.\n|woodie = It's uh, a moon rock.\n|maxwell = \"Moon\" rock.\n|wigfrid = A gift fröm Mani.\n|webber = Neat!\n|winona = Woah! What an odd texture.\n|warly = A little piece of sky to hold in my hand.\n|wortox = It was hewn from solid moon.\n|wormwood = Piece of Night Ball\n|wurt = Weird rock.\n|walter=It came from outer space!\n|wanda = I never would have predicted I'd see a piece of the moon up close.\n|choose = wolfgang}}\n'''Moon Rocks''' are [[Item]]s exclusive to ''[[Don't Starve Together]]''. They are obtained by mining crash-landed [[Meteor]]s, which have the appearance of sharp rocks striped with jagged blue cracks, or [[Suspicious Moonrock]] sculptures. Mining a [[Moonrock Boulder|Meteor Boulder]] will yield a [[Rocks|Rock]], a [[Flint]], and 2 Moon Rocks. There is a 60% chance for a third, and a 30% chance for a fourth Moon Rock.\n\nMoon Rocks can be crafted into [[Moon Rock Wall]]s, [[Cratered Moonrock]]s, [[Moon Dial]]s, [[Moon Rock Idol]]s and [[Moon Crater Turf]]. They are also required to repair the [[Moon Stone]], and to complete construction on upgrading the [[Florid Postern]] to the [[Celestial Portal]].\n\nMoon Rock can also be crafted by Wilson with 2 Marble after unlocking the \"[[Transmute Ore III]]\" skill.\n\n=={{pic|32|Icon Tools}} Usage==\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Moon Rock\n|count1 = 4\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Moon Rock Wall\n|resultcount = 4\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Moon Rock\n|count1 = 3\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Cratered Moonrock}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Moon Rock\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Blue Moonlens\n|item3 = Ice\n|count3 = 2\n|tool = Prestihatitator\n|result = Moon Dial}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Moon Rock\n|item2 = Purple Gem\n|tool = Celestial Orb\n|result = Moon Rock Idol}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Moon Rock\n|item2 = Moon Shard\n|count2 = 2\n|tool = Celestial Altar\n|result = Moon Crater Turf\n|resultcount = 4}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Moon Rock\n|item2 = Moon Shroom\n|count2 = 2\n|tool = Celestial Altar\n|result = Mutated Fungal Turf\n|resultcount = 4}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Moon Rock\n|count1 = 20\n|item2 = Purple Moonlens\n|result = Celestial Portal\n|note = Constructed by placing {{Pic|32|Portal Paraphernalia}} on {{Pic|32|Florid Postern}}}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Moon Rock\n|item2 = Blue Gem\n|result = Freeze Rounds\n|resultcount = 20\n|tool = Prestihatitator\n|character = Walter\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Moon Rock\n|item2 = Purple Gem\n|result = Slow-Down Rounds\n|resultcount = 20\n|tool = Shadow Manipulator\n|character = Walter\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Moon Rock\n|item2 = Thulecite\n|result = Astral Detector\n|tool = Blueprint (rare)\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Moon Rock\n|item2 = Thulecite Fragments\n|result = Ancient Stonework\n|resultcount = 4\n|tool = Blueprint (rare)\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Moon Rock\n|item2 = Thulecite Fragments\n|result = Ancient Sanctum Stonework\n|resultcount = 4\n|tool = Blueprint (rare)\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Moon Rock\n|item2 = Thulecite Fragments\n|result = Replica Sanctum Vase\n|tool = Blueprint (rare)\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Moon Rock\n|count1 = 5\n|item2 = Moon Shard\n|count2 = 5\n|item3 = Pure Brilliance\n|count3 = 1\n|result = Brightsmithy Kit\n|tool = Celestial Altar\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|tool = Brightsmithy\n|item4 = Spark Ark\n|item2 = Thick Fur\n|item3 = Pure Brilliance\n|count3 = 3\n|item1 = Moon Rock\n|count1 = 5\n|result = Polar Bearger Bin\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|tool = Brightsmithy\n|item4 = Spark Ark\n|item2 = Moon Shard\n|count2 = 8\n|item3 = Pure Brilliance\n|count3 = 3\n|item1 = Moon Rock\n|count1 = 5\n|result= Ice Crystaleyezer Kit\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|tool = Brightsmithy\n|item4 = Spark Ark\n|item2 = Brightshade Husk\n|count2 = 3\n|item3= Pure Brilliance\n|count3= 3\n|item1 = Moon Rock\n|count1 = 3\n|result= Howlitzer\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Moon Rock\n|count1 = 4\n|item2 = Cookie Cutter Shell\n|count2 = 4\n|tool = Crabby Hermit\n|result = Hermit Rehomer\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Moon Rock\n|count1 = 3\n|item2 = Moon Shard\n|count2 = 5\n|item3 = Cookie Cutter Shell\n|count3 = 5\n|tool = Crabby Hermit\n|result = Combriner\n}}\n\n=={{pic32|Placeholder}} Trivia==\n[[File:Moon Rock outdated.png|thumb|Old Moon Rock icon.]]\n* Moon Rocks are considered to be part of ''[[A New Reign]]'', even though they were introduced before the official start of the beta branch in the ''[[Don't Starve Together/Version History#November 5, 2014 - ...In with the New|...In with the New]]'' update.\n* In the ''[[A New Reign#September 1, 2016 - A Little Fixer Upper|A Little Fixer Upper]]'' update, the textures for Moon Rocks and all related items were updated.\n* Even though Moon Rocks are not available in the singleplayer game, [[Characters]] introduced with the ''[[Don't Starve: Hamlet|Hamlet]]'' DLC have unused examination quotes for them.\n{{Quotes\n|wagstaff = Evidentaly, useful minerals can be extracted from it.\n|warbucks = If I'm not mistaken, that is a bit of the moon!\n|wilba = 'TIS ROCK O' MOON BITS\" \n|choose = wagstaff}}\n{{Quotes\n|wagstaff = Fascinating! These are nothing like the meteorites I've seen.\n|warbucks = I say! A rather intriguing bit of geology!\n|wilba = A ROCK O' YON MOON\n|choose = wagstaff}}\n\n=={{Pic|32|Blueprint}} Gallery==\n<gallery captionalign=\"center\" hideaddbutton=\"true\">\n\nMining Moon Rocks.png|Several Moon Rocks next to a Meteor Boulder.\nMoon Rock Walls.png|Old Moon Rock texture items beside some Moon Rock Walls.\nFile:Early Moon Rock.jpg|An early texture for the Moon Rock as shown in the \"...In With The New\" update trailer.\n\n</gallery>\n<tabber>\nResources=\n{{Resources}}\n|-|\nCraftable Items=\n{{Craftable Items and Structures on DST}}\n|-|\nFood=\n{{Food}}\n</tabber>\n[[fr:Roche lunaire]]\n[[zh:月岩]]\n[[Category:Resources]]\n[[Category:Minerals]]\n[[Category:Items]]\n[[Category:A New Reign]]\n[[Category:Boss Dropped Items]]"
